<p>Two (ostensible) errors I found:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>carrying them. on its back</p>
</blockquote>
<blockquote>
<p>The air was think</p>
</blockquote>
<p>But still, fantastic story, absolutely. This line:</p>
<blockquote>
<p>And don't call me Shirley.</p>
</blockquote>
<p>made me laugh. I hope that was intended. Besides a captivating premise and great use of various SCPs, this was very well written, although there was a point (I believe when they were riding Gregory) that I wasn't entirely sure what exactly was going on.</p>
<p>As well, they got out of mirror-77 and went to reminisce? Didn't they talk about the possibility of subterfuge in how charito-tron was able to escape containment? That seems like a pressing concern, but they don't touch on it.</p>
<p>All in all, I enjoyed the piece, as I do with almost all of your writing. +1 from me.</p>

